variable.name: IDTYPE
variable.comment: IDTYPE and ID taken together form a unique study participant identification number.

variable.name: ABLIM1
variable.description: Actin binding LIM protein 1 (sample type: plasma)
variable.comment: The lower detectable limit for ABLIM1 is 1.23E+03 pg/mL and the upper detectable limit is 3.02E+05 pg/mL. ABLIM1 values below or above these limits were set to the lower or upper detectable limit respectively. Use ABLIM1_I to see what records are below and above these limits. No outliers for either cohort or both cohorts combined.

variable.name: ABLIM1_CV
variable.description: CV for actin binding LIM protein 1
variable.comment: No outliers for either cohort or both cohorts combined.

variable.name: ALAS2
variable.comment: The lower detectable limit for ALAS2 is 1.78E+03 pg/mL and the upper detectable limit is 4.34E+05 pg/mL. ALAS2 values below or above these limits were set to the lower or upper detectable limit respectively. Use ALAS2_I to see what records are below and above these limits. No outliers for either cohort or both cohorts combined.

variable.name: ALAS2_CV
variable.comment: No outliers for either cohort or both cohorts combined.

variable.name: PNP
variable.comment: The lower detectable limit for PNP is 7.22E+03 pg/mL and the upper detectable limit is 2.01E+06 pg/mL. PNP values below or above these limits were set to the lower or upper detectable limit respectively. Use PNP_I to see what records are below and above these limits. PNP values were set to unknown if PNP_CV was greater than or equal to 81.5 for Gen 3 (IDTYPE = 3). No outliers for Offspring (IDTYPE= 1).

variable.name: PNP_CV
variable.comment: PNP values were set to unknown if PNP_CV was greater than or equal to 81.5 for Gen 3 (IDTYPE = 3). No outliers for Offspring (IDTYPE= 1).

variable.name: RUNX1
variable.comment: The lower detectable limit for RUNX1 is 4.91E+03 pg/mL and the upper detectable limit is 6.67E+05 pg/mL. RUNX1 values below or above these limits were set to the lower or upper detectable limit respectively. Use RUNX1_I to see what records are below and above these limits. RUNX1 values were set to unknown if RUNX1_CV was greater than or equal to 132.0 for Gen 3 (IDTYPE = 3). No outliers for Offspring (IDTYPE= 1).

variable.name: RUNX1_CV
variable.comment: RUNX1 values were set to unknown if RUNX1_CV was greater than or equal to 132.0 for Gen 3 (IDTYPE = 3). No outliers for Offspring (IDTYPE= 1).

variable.name: TSC22D3
variable.description: TSC22 domain family, member 3 (sample type: plasma)
variable.comment: The lower detectable limit for TSC22D3 is 9.74E+02 pg/mL and the upper detectable limit is 2.32E+05 pg/mL. TSC22D3 values below or above these limits were set to the lower or upper detectable limit respectively. Use TSC22D3_I to see what records are below and above these limits. TSC22D3 values were set to unknown if TSC22D3_CV was greater than or equal to 1496 for Gen 3 (IDTYPE = 3) No outliers for Offspring (IDTYPE= 1).

variable.name: TSC22D3_CV
variable.description: CV for TSC22D3 domain family, member 3
variable.comment: TSC22D3 values were set to unknown if TSC22D3_CV was greater than or equal to 1496 for Gen 3 (IDTYPE = 3) No outliers for Offspring (IDTYPE= 1).

variable.name: RUN_DATE
variable.comment: Date includes month, day and year, however coding manual displays only month and year to preserve confidentiality.
